    "summary": "MX exposes multiple HTTP APIs—Platform API (OpenAPI), Data Enhancement Off Platform, MDX Real Time, MDX On Demand v5, Migration, Reporting, legacy Nexus and Atrium, plus a Batch SFTP interface—with auth primarily via Client Dashboard-issued `client_id` + `api_key` (Basic auth for Platform, `MD-API-KEY` plus `client_id` in path/query for several legacy APIs), Nexus session tokens from SSO, MX-provisioned Batch SFTP credentials, and MX-provisioned HMAC keys for MDX On Demand.",
    "credentials": {
      "mx_client_api_key": {
        "type": "basic",
        "label": "MX client ID + API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://dashboard.mx.com/sign_in",
        "setup": "Sign in to the [Client Dashboard](https://dashboard.mx.com/sign_in). Under [Client Dashboard](https://docs.mx.com/resources/client-dashboard), use **Manage API Keys** to view/copy/rotate your development and production API keys, and note your `client_id` from the dashboard. MX docs state these values can be used with Basic auth for the Platform API, with `client_id` as the username and `api_key` as the password. Many legacy APIs also require the same `api_key` in an `MD-API-KEY` header and the `client_id` in the base URL or query string. Whitelist your source IPs in the dashboard before calling IP-restricted APIs.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "mx_nexus_session_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "MX Nexus session token",
        "setup": "This token is minted per user/session, not manually created in the dashboard. First obtain an API token from the [MX SSO API](https://docs.mx.com/api-reference/more-apis/sso/) and then exchange it by `POST`ing to Nexus `/sessions`, as described in [Nexus Authentication and Security](https://docs.mx.com/api-reference/nexus/overview/). The resulting session token is sent in the `MD-SESSION-TOKEN` header and expires after 30 minutes unless refreshed by use.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "mx_mdx_ondemand_hmac": {
        "type": "signature",
        "label": "MDX On Demand HMAC key",
        "setup": "For [MDX On Demand v5](https://docs.mx.com/api-reference/more-apis/mdx/mdx-on-demand/), MX provides a shared HMAC key during partner integration. Your implementation must verify `MDX-HMAC` and `Content-MD5` headers on requests from MX, and use the session flow described in the docs. The key is provided by MX in base64 and supports HMAC SHA1/SHA224/SHA256/SHA384/SHA512.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
    },
